metadata.name: Roe in the grass
metadata.description:
Roe in the grass. Black and white photography. (2012)

As the dawn light kisses the cold November hills, I wander alone, lost in the majesty of the landscape. Suddenly, at the curve of the hill, a tapestry of beauty unfolds before me. My heart races as I snap shot after shot, trying to capture the raw, intimate imperfection of the moment. These precious creatures, so at home in the wild, are a gift to my senses, a reminder of the breathtaking world that surrounds us.
